JOHANNESBURG - The Premier Soccer League charged both Orlando Pirates and Mamelodi Sundowns for the violent disruptions during a match between the two clubs at Loftus Versveld.PSL charges Mamelodi Sundowns FC and Orlando Pirates FC. pic.twitter.com/jrrEm1ylZdPirates face charges relating to the conduct of their supporters on 11 February 2017, while Sundowns face charges of failing to supply adequate security.READ: Violence erupts as Sundowns lead Pirates 6-0The PSL's decision comes after fans vented their fury with a pitch invasion as a rampant Sundowns took a 6-0 lead against Pirates. The match was subsequently halted with approximately eight minutes remaining, but resumed about an hour after the incident.eNCA